HEADWORD: Surveillance
<hw>Sur*veil"lance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr.
<ets>surveiller</ets> to watch over; <ets>sur</ets> over +
<ets>veiller</ets> to watch, L. <ets>vigilare</ets>. See <er>Sur-</er>,
and <er>Vigil</er>.]</ety> <def>Oversight; watch; inspection;
supervision.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That sort of <qex>surveillance</qex> of which . . . the young have
accused the old.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

